                <note rend="inline" type="source">Paris Peace Conf. 181.92/3: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                            <gloss type="to">Commission to Negotiate Peace</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1919-07-25T18:00:00-04:00"
                            >July 25, 1919—6 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received July 26—10 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>2636. Your 3231 and 3222 [<hi rend="italic">3232?</hi>] and 3239.<note n="1"
                        xml:id="d256fn1">None printed.</note> President has approved that army
                    officer be detailed to represent the United States on mission to Hungary.
                    General Bliss may make the selection from list which he has.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Lansing</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
